        <num>CC 2987</num>
        <heading>2987.  Procuration defined; person to whom addressed</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2987.  Procuration defined; person to whom addressed
A procuration is a unilateral juridical act by which a person, the principal, confers authority on another person, the representative, to represent the principal in legal relations.
The procuration may be addressed to the representative or to a person with whom the representative is authorized to represent the principal in legal relations.</p>
        </content>
